entry.title: Rework on CapsLock key event rewriting
entry.content:
Currently, on ChromeOS, CapsLock key is handled in the following way.

Assuming a user

- Presses CapsLock

- Releases CapsLock

- Presses A

- Releases A

- Presses CapsLock

- Releases CapsLock

- Presses A

- Releases A



in this order, then we will see

- CapsLock press w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- CapsLock release ... (1)

- A press w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- A release w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- CapsLock press w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- CapsLock release

- A press

- A release

thus, so specifically around (1) EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON flag is flipped.



This CL makes the event as following:

- CapsLock press w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- CapsLock release w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- A press w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- A release w/ EF_CAPS_LOCK_ON

- CapsLock press

- CapsLock release

- A press

- A release



which is consistent with CapsLock key behavior on Windows platform.



BUG=b:314069634

TEST=Tryjob. Run the above scenario on DUT manually.

entry.title: [iOS] Only re-open NTP when app comes to foreground from background
entry.content:
There are a lot of scenarios when the NTP reopens automatically before

the user puts the app, including but not limited to



1. User takes a tour to the app switcher without really opening other

apps or go back to the home screen

2. (This is the most disturbing) User opens split window in iPad

3. User slides over the window



In all these cases, the scene leaves "foreground active" state while

never reaches the "background" state, but the app conditionally opens

NTP on each transition to the foreground. This CL adds a flag that is

TRUE when the scene enters background and FALSE when the scene is

activated, so on activation (before we update the flag) it can be known

whether this transition originates from the background or a temporary

inactivation.

entry.content:
Before this CL, only App Modal dialog is supported on CCT. This CL

adds Tab Modal dialog to CCT and tests whether they can be

correctly dismissed by navigation and back press.



This CL also adds a default enabled flag.

In previous CL, since PWA/TWA extends BaseCCTActivity, they can also

request to show a tab modal dialog. But since there is no browser

UI on PWA/TWA, the tab modal dialog is always suspended and no dialog

is shown as a result.



This CL fixes that by only allowing CCTActivity to initialize a

tab modal handler, such that CCT can now a tab modal dialog and

PWA/TWA is still only allowed to show APP modal dialogs.

entry.title: Estimate Attempted Synchronized Scrolling
entry.content:
This change attempts to detect when a page is attempting to

synchronize an effect in response to scroll deltas. We consider

it a possible attempt, if a) there is a scroll handler (otherwise

we would not have attempted to synchronize), b) we access scroll

position, and c) make an update. It's also possible for this

update to be accomplished using requestAnimationFrame (i.e., the

scroll handler might use rAF to realize the update), so this

heuristic also observers for scroll position accesses and updates

during rAF, but only if a rAF was scheduled during a scroll

handler. This may be inaccurate since we're not tracking exactly

which handler was scheduled from scroll, however.



For privacy review see http://go/phgfy



credit: flackr@ for both suggesting this check and the approach to

the heuristic (eg, checking for any mutation when we've observed

scroll offsets, how to observe rAF being scheduled during scroll

handlers and only considering rAF in this case). Credit to

sullivan@ for suggesting UKM, and to jbroman@ for suggesting the

approach to instrumenting methods in c++ and using ImplementedAs in

order to distinguish calls from JS.

entry.title: Renaming map elements no longer breaks accessibility tree
entry.content:
The original test which should have caught this failure was

turned off here for being flakey:

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/2679285



The failure was do to some mistaken logic in this CL (which landed

two days earlier and only passed sometimes do to a race condition

where the accessibility tree was only built after the map is

re-named, thus the test appearing flakey):

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/2679285



That is to say: maps could not be renamed without breaking the

accessibility tree for almost three years.



This CL:

- Fixes the bug by triggering a `kRoleChangeFromRoleOrType` update

on the image element (which has a corresponding AXObject).

Previously, the update was called on a map element, which has no

AXObject, and updates in tree_update_callback_queue_main_ which

do not have AXObjects associated with them are not processed.

- Update the test file in order to more easily understand the output

of the test when inspecting visually.

entry.title: [layout] Respect align-self/justify-self for abspos elements.
entry.content:
This fixes the bug that we weren't respecting align-self/justify-self

for abspos elements with both insets set.



Instead of just using the containing block "start" inset bias when

both insets are set - look at the value of align-self/justify-self

(see logic in GetAlignmentInsetBias).



Tests are validating the following:

- {align,justify}-self-*.html -> validates the correct position with

different writing-mode combinations and *-self keywords. (Tests the

complex logic in GetAlignmentInsetBias).

- safe-{align,justify}-self-*.html -> validates the safe/unsafe

behaviour with different writing-mode combinations, and "safe end".

(Tests the clamping logic in ComputeInsets).

- stretch-intrinsic-size-*.html -> validates the correct aspect-ratio

handling for stretching one axes, and the size being reflexed in

the opposite axis, with different writing-mode combinations. (Tests

the logic in ComputeOof*Dimensions and the replaced logic in

out_of_flow_layout_part.cc).

- table-{align,justify}-self-stretch.html -> validates correct table

stretching behaviour, and that tables still respect their implicit

min-intrinsic size constraint.



Placed behind blink flag: LayoutAlignForPositioned
